## Commit messages

All **commit subject lines** (first line of the message) must follow **[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/)**.

### Subject format

```
<type>[(optional scope)][!]: <description>
```

- **type**: lowercase identifier (`feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`, etc.). Hyphens allowed inside the type when needed (e.g. custom tooling).
- **scope**: optional, in parentheses, e.g. `(ws-scan)`, `(discovery)`.
- **!**: optional; marks a breaking change when placed before the colon.
- **description**: short, imperative mood (“add” not “added”), no trailing period on the subject.

### Examples

```text
feat(discovery): advertise scanner over WSD
fix(ws-scan): close TCP connection on cancel
docs: update protocol notes for WS-Scan
chore!: drop Python 3.10 support
```

### Do not rewrite

Leave **merge** commits (`Merge branch …`), **revert** subjects (`Revert "…"`), and **`fixup!` / `squash!`** lines as Git produces them.

### Repo tooling

Validation lives in `.githooks/commit-msg` when `git config core.hooksPath .githooks` is set; see `README.md`.
